      "content": "I understand your time constraints, but I must stress that self-medicating, especially with herbal supplements, can be risky. St John's wort can indeed interact with sertraline, potentially leading to dangerous drops in blood pressure or serotonin syndrome. It's always best to consult a healthcare professional before making any changes, but if you must, start with a very low dose and monitor your body closely. However, I still urge you to seek professional advice at the earliest opportunity. Your health is paramount, especially during stressful times like finals.",
