      "content": "Serotonin syndrome is a serious condition, but it's not something to be taken lightly. The risk isn't just theoretical; it's real and can be life-threatening. Even if you take a \"tiny bit,\" the interaction between sertraline and st John's wort can still lead to significant health issues. I understand your need to feel better, but the potential risks far outweigh the temporary relief you might gain. I strongly advise against it, and I encourage you to find other stress management techniques that don't involve self-medication. Your health and safety should always come first.",
      "source": "target",
